{"key":"processedPost-16484271","value":{"id":16484271,"first":16483543,"last":16507032,"when":1341496333,"utime":"07/05/12 04:52 PM","cleanedPost":"There are no exact ratios which work better than any other ratio.&nbsp; It's species dependent and even strain dependent, assuming you have an isolated strain to experiment with.<br />Bulk substrate ingredients which can grow all by themselves can be used in any quantity you have available.&nbsp; Keep coffee grinds to half or less of any substrate mix, and vermiculite can be used at up to half by volume to provide minerals and water retention.<br />Don't use blood meal or veg oil despite claims you'll read.&nbsp; I've not seen any good come from those two in any quantity.<br />RR"}}